<b>Pipérade</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../679/3789679.xml">
Basque</link> dish typically prepared with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../258/51258.xml">
onion</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../979/55979.xml">
sweet peppers</link>, and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../234/9940234.xml">
tomatoes</link> <link>
sautéd</link> in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>. It may be a main or side dish.  Typical additions include <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../010/19196010.xml">
egg</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../469/50469.xml">
garlic</link> or meats such as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../299/14299.xml">
ham</link>.
